---
title: Lean Mean Chicken and Greens with Rosemary Potatoes and Gremolata
description: Don’t let the name intimidate you: gremolata is a gussied-up name for an easy-to-make herb condiment that tastes fresh like a spring day. It breathes new life into this simple meal of chicken and potatoes. On the side, you’ve also got a cheerful salad of arugula, cranberries, and walnuts in a lemony dressing—just the thing to put a happy, hearty smile on your face!
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/chicken-paillard-w07-863dcd3d.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/chicken-paillard-w07-fe57dfc6.pdf
time required: 30 minutes
nutrition:
  calories: 650 kcal
